      "message": "Not for this CL, but this reminds me of previous conversations, and the somewhat dangerous intrinsic handling in several backends (where we just check the map for a function name and assume it\u0027s the intrinsic). I think the actual logic we should be applying everywhere (for a function call) is roughly:\n\nif (function.isBuiltin() \u0026\u0026 !function.hasDefinition()) { /* look up in intrinsic map, etc... */ }\n\nelse { /* treat it as a normal function call */ }\n\nDoes that make sense? It should let us be much more confident that the calls we\u0027re handling when we get into our intrinsic-specific code in each backend will only see the signatures declared in sksl_gpu/sksl_public.sksl.",
